This is file zcms.doc.
For IBM CMS systems, proceed as follows.

 1. Transfer all files from the MINOS floppy disk to a disk of your choice.

 2. Compile all the Fortran files, creating TEXT files.

 3. Load the MINOS TEXT files
       mi10mach, mi15blas, ... mi80ncon
    into a library called MINOS TXTLIB.

 4. Write an EXEC to define run-time files and load the relevant
    main program and nonlinear functions.
    For example, the following is suitable for running MINOS on the
    nonlinear test problem "t5weapon":

       GLOBAL TXTLIB    VFORTLIB MINOS
       GLOBAL LOADLIB   VFLODLIB
       FILEDEF  4 DISK  T5WEAPON SPC     '*'
       FILEDEF  6 DISK  TERMINAL
       FILEDEF  9 DISK  T5WEAPON LISTING  A
       FILEDEF 10 DISK  T5WEAPON MPS     '*'
       FILEDEF 11 DISK  T5WEAPON BASIS    A '(' RECFM FB  LRECL 80
       FILEDEF 12 DISK  T5WEAPON NEWBASIS A '(' RECFM FB  LRECL 80
       LOAD MI00MAIN, MI05FUNS '(' NOMAP START

 5. Follow the general guidelines in m1minos.doc.
